The `createFileSystemWatcher` is declared like this:

```typescript
export function createFileSystemWatcher(globPattern: string, ignoreCreateEvents?: boolean, ignoreChangeEvents?: boolean, ignoreDeleteEvents?: boolean): FileSystemWatcher;
```

But if I run this:

```typescript
const watcher1 = vscode.workspace.createFileSystemWatcher("**/somethingInteresting", false, false, false);
console.log(watcher1.ignoreChangeEvents);
console.log(watcher1.ignoreCreateEvents);
console.log(watcher1.ignoreDeleteEvents);

const watcher2 = vscode.workspace.createFileSystemWatcher("**/somethingBoring", true, true, true);
console.log(watcher2.ignoreChangeEvents);
console.log(watcher2.ignoreCreateEvents);
console.log(watcher2.ignoreDeleteEvents);
```

I get this output:

```
true
true
true
false
false
false
```

It is probably easy to fix, but if anybody are actually using those properties, it would be a serious breaking change.
